sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI opt
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cI repressor from Lambda phage optimized for E. coli cI (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
cI repressor from Lambda phage optimized for E. coli cI (+LVA).
Preferential codons for better expression into E. coli.
Includes LVA tag.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Rodriguez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Sequence was obtained form BioBrick BBa_C0052, it was optimized changing for preferential codons as possible and then synthesized.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Search for illegal sites for classic BioBricks was performed, they were detected and eliminated.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091105
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This promoter is a modified version of the Mnt promoter that is also responsive to TetR. The promoter should be repressed by Mnt repressor. It should also be repressed by TetR, and in the absence of Mnt repressor, should be induced by aTc.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Robert Cool
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part comes from the Mnt promoter and the TetR promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Mnt repressor binds as a tetramer to two half-operator sites. Introduction of TetR binding sites between the Mnt promoter -10 sequence and the start site for transcription should allow for repression by TetR. Accordingly, the hybrid promoter was designed by 1) Remove all bases of mnt promoter 3??? to -10: gagtcgtattaattt will be replaced by tccctatcagtgata, and 2) truncate the second half of ptet -10 and mutate -35 so that it function to bind tetR (replace ttgaca with actgta), but is not a promoter, and 3) place the tetR1 and tetR2 binding sites 3??? to truncated mnt -10 sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: OL region form Lambda phage. It is used to allow a construction to be controlled dually by cI protein. cI protein may interact with pRM promoter and OL region in order to form an octameric structure which permits, first the activation of transcription from pRM promoter and then effectively repression from it as well.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Rodriguez, Eduardo Almeyda, Porfirio Quintero
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes directly from genomic DNA of Lambda phage. It was extracted by PCR as recommended by the Registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Analysis of illegal restriction sites was performed, but it does not have them originally.
